---
// Components
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header";
import Hero from "../components/Hero";
import AppShowcase from "../components/AppShowcase";
import Footer from "../components/Footer";

// Styles
import "../styles/main.scss";
---

<Layout title="Bibliophile | Privacy Policy">
	<Header client:load />

	<main>
    <section>
      <h1>Privacy Policy for Bibliophile</h1>
      <p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> December 23, 2024</p>
  
      <p><strong>Welcome to Bibliophile!</strong></p>
      <p>Bibliophile ("we," "our," "us") values your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our app, website, or related services (collectively, the "Services").</p>
  
      <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
  
      <p>We collect the following types of information to provide and improve our Services:</p>
  
      <h3>1.1 Personal Information You Provide:</h3>
      <ul>
          <li>Name, email address, and other account details when you register.</li>
          <li>Preferences, reading lists, reviews, and other content you create.</li>
          <li>Payment information for purchases or subscriptions (processed securely by third-party providers).</li>
      </ul>
  
      <h3>1.2 Automatically Collected Information:</h3>
      <ul>
          <li>Device information, such as IP address, operating system, and device type.</li>
          <li>Usage data, including time spent on the app, pages viewed, and interaction logs.</li>
          <li>Cookies and similar technologies to track activity and enhance user experience.</li>
      </ul>
  
      <h3>1.3 Third-Party Information:</h3>
      <ul>
          <li>Data from integrated services like Google, Apple, or Facebook if you choose to log in using these platforms.</li>
      </ul>
  
      <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
  
      <p>We use your information for purposes including but not limited to:</p>
      <ul>
          <li>Providing access to and improving our Services.</li>
          <li>Personalizing content recommendations based on your preferences.</li>
          <li>Communicating with you about updates, offers, and customer support.</li>
          <li>Ensuring security and detecting fraudulent or unauthorized activity.</li>
          <li>Complying with legal obligations.</li>
      </ul>
  
      <h2>3. Sharing Your Information</h2>
  
      <p>We do not sell your personal information. However, we may share your information with:</p>
      <ul>
          <li><strong>Service Providers:</strong> Companies that help us operate the app, such as payment processors or cloud storage providers.</li>
          <li><strong>Business Partners:</strong> Partners providing promotions or co-branded services.</li>
          <li><strong>Legal Authorities:</strong> When required to comply with legal obligations or enforce our terms.</li>
      </ul>
  
      <h2>4. Your Choices</h2>
  
      <p>You have control over your information:</p>
      <ul>
          <li><strong>Access and Update:</strong> Edit your profile and account details at any time.</li>
          <li><strong>Opt-Out:</strong> Unsubscribe from promotional emails via the link provided in the email.</li>
          <li><strong>Delete Account:</strong> Request the deletion of your account and data by contacting support at <a href="mailto:support@bibliophile.com">support@bibliophile.com</a>.</li>
          <li><strong>Cookies:</strong> Manage cookie preferences through your browser settings.</li>
      </ul>
  
      <h2>5. Data Security</h2>
  
      <p>We implement reasonable security measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure. However, no method of transmission over the internet is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>
  
      <h2>6. Third-Party Links</h2>
  
      <p>Our Services may contain links to third-party websites or services. We are not responsible for their privacy practices, and we encourage you to review their policies.</p>
  
      <h2>7. Children's Privacy</h2>
  
      <p>Bibliophile is not intended for users under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect information from children. If you believe a child has provided us with personal information, please contact us to delete it.</p>
  
      <h2>8. International Users</h2>
  
      <p>By using Bibliophile, you consent to your information being processed in [Insert Country], where privacy laws may differ from those in your location.</p>
  
      <h2>9. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
  
      <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any significant changes by posting the updated policy on our app and website, and, if applicable, notifying you via email.</p>
  
      <h2>10. Contact Us</h2>
  
      <p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us at:</p>
      <address>
          Bibliophile Support<br>
          Email: <a href="mailto:bibliolabsofficial@gmail.com">bibliolabsofficial@gmail.com</a><br>
          Address: bibliolabsofficial@gmail.com
      </address>
  
      <p>Thank you for trusting Bibliophile!</p>
    </section>
	</main>
</Layout>

<Footer />
